  "title": "Production Operator x 5 ($2500) Tuas",
  "description": "<p><strong>Working location: Tuas (Transport at Boon Lay)</strong><br /><strong>Working hours*: 1st shift (0730 – 1630) / 2nd Shift (1630 – 0130) / 3rd Shift (2030 – 0530) </strong><br /><strong>*</strong><em><strong>Can choose fixed or if can rotating will be good. </strong></em></p><p><u><strong>Role and Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li> To perform product assembly and testing in production line.</li><li> To comply with production Job Breakdown Sheet and Work Instruction; Quality Instructions and Environment, Health & Safety (EHS) Instructions.</li><li>To feedback to production shift supervisor for any deviation concerning quality, machine breakdown, safety.</li><li>To alert maintenance department about machine breakdown through E-Andon platform.</li><li>To perform steps of 5S at your assigned workstations.</li><li>To perform support for sorting of defective components or finished goods.</li><li>To participate in continuous improvement or Kaizen events and provide feedback on ways to improve current work process.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Skills and Qualifications</strong></u></p><ul><li>Upper Secondary School or High School or equivalent.</li><li>Know how to use computer (need to use Manufacturing Execution System software)</li><li>Good problem-solving skills</li></ul>",
